               <head>Poems in Judeo-Persian by Yuhannah Mirza Dawud</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85103704">
                  <summary>A collection of poems in Judeo-Persian.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="jpr" />
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1v" to="132r" />
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf_97488913 http://viaf.org/viaf/97488913">יוחנה
                                    דאוד</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf_97488913 http://viaf.org/viaf/97488913">Ben David
                                    Dawud, Yuhanna Mirza, 1885-1969</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="he">קול דוד</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḳol Daṿid</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <explicit />
                     <note>
                        <p>Autograph.</p>
                        <p>Yuhanna Dawud, known as Yohanan ben David in Hebrew and John
                                    David in English; a traditional Jew from a religious background;
                                    collected Persian works of art and Islamic treasures from his
                                    boyhood; Professor of Oriental Art and Literature; oriental
                                    translator; Curator of the Department of Islamic Art, British
                                    Museum; died London, 1969. </p>
                     </note>
                     <colophon />
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>Paper codex of the 20th century.</p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Paper with laid lines and chain lines.</support>
                        <extent>132 folios (no flyleaves)<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>258</height>
                              <width>201</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>140</height>
                              <width>82</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>Foliation in Arabic numerals in pencil.</p>
                           <p>Parallel pagination in ink by the scribe: ff. 1v-2v: in Roman
                                        numerals, ff. 3r-131v: Hebrew characters.</p>
                        </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>No catchwords.</p>
                        </collation>
                        <condition>
                           <p />
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="10" writtenLines="10">
                           <p>Uniform laoyout.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc hands="1">
                     <summary>Persian Hebrew square script of the 20th century; in black ink,
                                certain passages are underlined in red. Scribe: Yuhanna
                                Dawud.</summary>
                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole" />
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>
                        <p>Full-page illustration on f. 1v: God's name and a menorah.</p>
                        <p>Golden inscriptions: f. 1r: title and author of the book and a
                                    Magen David; f. 132r: <quote xml:lang="he">יהוה הוא אלהים יהוה
                                        הוא אלהים</quote>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Photograph of a book binding glued onto the front pastedown.</p>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p />
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding>
                        <p>Post-1600, brown stamped leather binding with embossed figures;
                                    two metal clasps. At the bottom of the front pastedown, 'Moritz
                                    Mädler Leipzig W'. Perhaps identical with <persName>Moritz
                                        Mädler</persName>, the suitcase and fine leathergoods
                                    maker.
                        </p>
                        <p />
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <accMat>
                     <p />
                  </accMat>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin notBefore="1900" notAfter="1969">
                     <date>20th century (not after 1969)</date>
                     <origPlace>England (London)</origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Note on a blue leaf pasted onto the back pastedown: '"The Voice of
                                David:" <quote xml:lang="he">קול דוד</quote> An original autograph
                                manuscript, written in Judaeo-Persian, on 259 pages, 10 lines to a
                                page, in gilt stamped leather binding, with embossed figures and
                                religious emblems, especially, a bust of Albrecht Dürer, made by the
                                celebrated book-binder Moritz Madler of Leipzig. Contents: Prayers
                                of thanksfulness, and praises for God's blessings as His gifts to
                                mankind. Rejoicing in the love behind life, the purpose through it,
                                and the assured hope ahead of it.'
                     </p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Acquisition note on back pastedown at the bottom of the pasted note:
                                'Presented to the British Museum, Department of Oriental Printed
                                Books and Manuscripts. <persName>Y.Dawud</persName>.' Another
                                aquisition note on f. 132v: 'Presented by Mīrzā Yūhḥannā Dāʾūd 18.
                                iii. 1958.' Date of accession 19 March 1958.
                     </p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
